channel.title: Unidentified Network
channel.description:
Hey guys, I`m currently on my mobile phone so I`m gonna try and keep this thread short and to the point.
I`m staying at a Hotel in North Carolina at the moment and when I attempt to connect to there unsecured internet wifi a box pops up saying the connection was unsuccessful "this computer currently has limited connectivity to *hotelsinternet*."
Then, when I hover over the wifi connection bar at the bottom right, it has a caution triangle over it and its showing all 4 bars but it says "unidentified network" "no internet access". Not only that but it shows that its recieving packets but were not sending any?
im not a tech wiz at all when it comes to this so any detailed explanation would be very nice and appreciated. I would go to google for this but as I said im on my mobile which makes it very difficult.
